		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64156011"><p><div class="quote"><p> <em> complaining that the fines create a "regime" that would "stifle innovation," and urging Congress to repeal it.</em> </p><p>It's always amusing when a company trots out the whole, "It will stifle innovation if we have to do  . .<nobr> <wbr></nobr>." </p></div><p>
To be fair, I imagine this actually will stifle new/innovative ways companies might use to *avoid* capturing methane.<nobr> <wbr></nobr>:-)   More seriously, while it may be more hassle and less profitable to capture methane rather than let it leak and/or flair it off, there are <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Methane#Uses" title="wikipedia.org">uses</a> [wikipedia.org] for it if companies would stop being lazy and take a long(er) term look at things -- don't the SpaceX <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SpaceX_Raptor" title="wikipedia.org">Raptor engines</a> [wikipedia.org] burn methane?  Those Starships are going to need a bunch of it...</p></div>
	</div>

